						               													<description>G.G.A. Granny Grating Armies is a rule set designed to be used with 10mm miniatures in the ancient world, the book contains rules so that you can conduct structured and abstract command based games. &amp;#10;Give your armies commands and watch as they complete them in battle! &amp;#10;GGA is directly inspired by the video game and infamous program &amp;quot;rome total war&amp;quot; which was in turn inspired by the BBC tv show &amp;quot;time commanders&amp;quot;. &amp;#10;GGA is also well known for it's innovative &amp;quot;granny grating army&amp;quot; style of home made miniature making. The book is worth grabbing for the tutorials alone which have inspired people all across the world.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Home made hosts of soldiers built in a matter of hours with the GGA system. No need to ever wait weeks for a delivery again, simply craft an army and get gaming. &amp;quot;wargaming on your terms&amp;quot;. &amp;#10;GGA is effective, elegant and boasts a unique energy and command point system. With mechanics in place to help emulate real warfare, you must be tactical and strategic. Simple to learn and enthusing to master the game brings to the tabletop a system like no other. Can you keep your army enegised and ready to go? Or will your war host burn out and fall to the whim of your enemy?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;INCLUDES&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Four Army lists to get you started: Romans, Spartans, Celts and Egyptians.&amp;#10;     A comprehensive command grid to utilise in battle.&amp;#10;     All the tokens and markers you need to play.  &amp;#10;     Instructions on how to build your own infantry, cavalry and archers.&amp;#10;     Grannies History helps to keep you engaged with history!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
